      "message": "Do we care about this check? The next malloc will fail anyway in this case, and even if it didn\u0027t it isn\u0027t possible for the caller to get outside the resulting allocation anyway (their own calculations would wrap around).\n\nNote that the allocator on Android will assert in release if asking for more than SSIZE_MAX. So maybe that\u0027s a better thing to check for before allocating? It\u0027s strange to have any allocation where ptrdiff_t can\u0027t actually represent all the diffs.",
