      "writtenOn": "2017-10-06T18:15:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This check seems interesting. Currently SkData internally uses \u0027::operator new\u0027 so it should fail or not return nullptr. Indeed, at the moment this will cause a release assert since it will detect overflow when computing the total required size. It seems like maybe we want SkData constructors to instead be based on a non-throwing malloc and return nullptr in these situations?\n\nIt\u0027s just odd that getting up (anywhere) near Sk_MaxSizeT will cause a release assert, but then overflowing will fail gracefully.",
